  "text": "The gRPC health check protocol implementation in Envoy v1.31.2 is primarily located in the source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc directory with supporting utilities in source/common/grpc and source/common/upstream. The core implementation centers on three main classes:\n\n1. **GrpcHealthCheckerFactory** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h/cc): A factory class registered as 'envoy.health_checkers.grpc' that creates instances of ProdGrpcHealthCheckerImpl. It implements the CustomHealthCheckerFactory interface and is registered via REGISTER_FACTORY macro.\n\n2. **GrpcHealthCheckerImpl** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h/cc): The main health checker implementation that extends HealthCheckerImplBase. It maintains references to the grpc.health.v1.Health service method descriptor and handles the gRPC health check configuration including service_name and authority from GrpcHealthCheck proto message.\n\n3. **GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h/cc): Inner struct managing individual health check sessions. It implements the request/response handling chain:\n   - onInterval(): Initiates health checks by creating a connection and constructing a grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckRequest\n   - decodeHeaders(): Validates HTTP/2 response headers and extracts gRPC status\n   - decodeData(): Parses the gRPC framed HealthCheckResponse using Grpc::Decoder\n   - decodeTrailers(): Extracts final gRPC status from trailers\n   - isHealthCheckSucceeded(): Validates that gRPC status is OK and HealthCheckResponse::status is SERVING\n   - onRpcComplete(): Handles health check completion and status logging\n   - logHealthCheckStatus(): Maps response status values (SERVING, NOT_SERVING, UNKNOWN, SERVICE_UNKNOWN)\n\nThe implementation uses gRPC protocol message types from src/proto/grpc/health/v1/health.pb.h:\n- grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckRequest: Contains optional service name field\n- grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse: Contains status field with enum values (UNKNOWN=0, SERVING=1, NOT_SERVING=2, SERVICE_UNKNOWN=3)\n\nHTTP/2 to gRPC status mapping is implemented via source/common/grpc/status.h/cc, specifically Utility::httpToGrpcStatus() which maps HTTP status codes to gRPC status codes per https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/doc/http-grpc-status-mapping.md. Additional utilities in source/common/grpc/common.h/cc provide:\n- isGrpcResponseHeaders(): Validates gRPC response format\n- getGrpcStatus(): Extracts gRPC status from headers/trailers\n- getGrpcMessage(): Extracts gRPC error messages\n- serializeToGrpcFrame(): Serializes HealthCheckRequest to gRPC wire format\n- prepareHeaders(): Constructs gRPC request headers with service and method names\n\nThe configuration is defined in api/envoy/config/core/v3/health_check.proto (and v2 legacy version) with the GrpcHealthCheck message containing service_name and authority fields, allowing configuration of which service to health check and the authority header value.\n\nFactory registration and creation is handled in source/common/upstream/health_checker_impl.cc where HealthCheckerFactory::create() dispatches to the registered 'envoy.health_checkers.grpc' factory when kGrpcHealthCheck is specified in the health check configuration."
}

